, synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[636,764,1208,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Discotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belzebuth">
<emphasis box="[636,764,1208,1230]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. belzebuth</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1274,1518]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,506,1274,1299]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Composition and distribution</emphasis>
. Six species, in Mindanao—the 
<collectingCountry box="[879,1005,1274,1299]" name="Philippines" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[1023,1168,1274,1299]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Discotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scabridus">
<emphasis box="[1023,1168,1274,1299]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. scabridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Borneo (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[1293,1436,1274,1299]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Discotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belzebuth">
<emphasis box="[1293,1436,1274,1299]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. belzebuth</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1909" box="[198,331,1310,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Discotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shelfordi">
<emphasis box="[198,331,1310,1335]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. shelfordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<collectingRegion box="[354,447,1311,1335]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[464,560,1310,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Discotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="selysi">
<emphasis box="[464,560,1310,1335]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. selysi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Metawei (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1898" box="[698,805,1310,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Discotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis box="[698,805,1310,1335]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and southern Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[1098,1201,1310,1335]" name="Malaysia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mahmood, Idris &amp; Salmah" authorityYear="2007" box="[1217,1357,1310,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Discotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="selangori">
<emphasis box="[1217,1357,1310,1335]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. selangori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1274,1518]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,266,1346,1371]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Notes</emphasis>
. The genus has recently been assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolívar" authorityYear="1887" box="[798,932,1346,1371]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Scelimenini">Scelimenini</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[954,1235,1346,1371]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref38959" refString="Skejo, J. &amp; Bertner, P. (2017) No more dust and exoskeletons-in vivo photographic records provide new data on Eufalconius pendleburyi Gunther, 1938 (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae) from the Titiwangsa Mts. Annales Zoologici, 67 (4), 665 - 672. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 00034541 ANZ 2017.67.4.003" type="journal article">Skejo &amp; Bertner, 2017</bibRefCitation>
), but the formal synonymization of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1907" box="[370,539,1382,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Discotettiginae">Discotettiginae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolívar" authorityYear="1887" box="[596,747,1382,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Scelimeninae">Scelimeninae</taxonomicName>
and revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1050,1171,1383,1406]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Discotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1050,1171,1383,1406]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Discotettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will soon be published (Skejo, Pushkar &amp; Tumbrinck in preparation). The genus is characteristic within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolívar" authorityYear="1887" box="[1082,1216,1418,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Scelimenini">Scelimenini</taxonomicName>
in having widened subapical antennal segments (6th to 8th or 9th) and large pronotal projections. It is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zheng, 1994" authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="1994" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Paragavialidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1246,1436,1457,1482]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Paragavialidium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[151,296,1493,1518]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref40480" refString="Zheng, Z. M. (1994) A new genus and three new species of Scelimenidae from China (Orthoptera: Terigoidea [Tetrigoidea]). Journal of Hubei University (Natural Science), 16 (1), 1 - 5." type="journal article">Zheng, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Serville, 1838)" authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" baseAuthorityName="Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[306,725,1493,1518]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Discotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belzebuth">
<emphasis box="[306,542,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Discotettix belzebuth</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[557,717,1493,1518]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref38644" refString="Serville, G. A. (1838 [1839]) Histoire naturelle des insectes. Orthopteres. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, xviii + 776 pp., 14 pls." type="book">Serville, 1838</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[740,806,1493,1518]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,956,978]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,934]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,195,934]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Alive Discotettix belzebuth (Serville, 1838) female, standing on a fallen leaf in Sarawak (Malaysia: Borneo). Photograph by Arthur Anker, reproduced with photographer's permission." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437975/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) is the species with the highest pronotal projections.
</paragraph>
